# Method format()
> [Read it at source](https://github.com/julien-boudry/Condorcet/blob/master/src/Utils/CondorcetUtil.php#L83)

```php
public static function CondorcetUtil::format( mixed $input, [ bool $convertObject = true ] ): mixed
```

## Description
Provides pretty re-formatting, human readable, of all Condorcet PHP objects or result sets.

Can be used before a var_dump, or just to get simpler data output.

## Parameters

### **input:**
```php
mixed $input
```
**Type:** `mixed`

Input to convert.

### **convertObject:**
```php
bool $convertObject = true
```
**Type:** `bool`

If true. Will convert Candidate objects into string representation of their name.

## Return
**Type:** `mixed`

New formatted data.
